The pink.

965
01:24:09,756 --> 01:24:12,350
Well, you're part
of this operation now.

966
01:24:12,525 --> 01:24:16,017
First we snuff everything that moves
out there, then we find your diamond.

967
01:24:16,196 --> 01:24:17,823
Colonel?

968
01:24:18,365 --> 01:24:20,799
Go get kitted. Yes?

969
01:24:27,107 --> 01:24:29,098
Move, move, move!

970
01:24:29,309 --> 01:24:32,574
-Go get your kit.
-Will do, chum. Will do.

971
01:24:36,116 --> 01:24:39,279
lt's go time, all right?
Meet me behind the tents.

972
01:24:42,389 --> 01:24:44,084
How's Benjamin?

973
01:24:44,257 --> 01:24:45,724
They say he'll live.

974
01:24:47,060 --> 01:24:48,322
Good. Good.

975
01:24:55,735 --> 01:24:57,532
Listen, Maddy...

976
01:24:58,938 --> 01:25:00,701
...l need you to do me one last favor.

977
01:25:01,741 --> 01:25:03,106
Yeah?

978
01:25:05,078 --> 01:25:06,739
Tell that guard
you wanna put him...

979
01:25:06,913 --> 01:25:09,575
...on the cover of Soldier of Fortune
magazine for me.

980
01:25:15,622 --> 01:25:16,850
You're going in.

981
01:25:21,261 --> 01:25:23,525
You and Solomon.

982
01:25:25,699 --> 01:25:26,688
You're going in now.

983
01:25:27,534 --> 01:25:29,729
Your plane leaves
in a few minutes, huh?

984
01:25:32,339 --> 01:25:34,307
You're an idiot.

985
01:25:38,611 --> 01:25:41,478
-What if l wanted to go in with you?
-l'd say no.

986
01:25:41,648 --> 01:25:43,639
-What if l insist?
-l'd insist back.

987
01:25:49,756 --> 01:25:50,950
lt's my story.

988
01:25:51,124 --> 01:25:54,525
Your story is Van De Kaap, all right?
That stone is mine.

989
01:25:54,694 --> 01:25:58,130
l'm not leaving here without it,
you understand?

990
01:25:59,599 --> 01:26:02,466
Please, just give me two minutes.

991
01:26:19,219 --> 01:26:20,618
Yeah.

992
01:26:31,931 --> 01:26:33,626
-Hello.
-Hi.

993
01:26:33,800 --> 01:26:37,031
My name is Maddy Bowen.
l'm with Vital Affairs magazine.

994
01:26:37,203 --> 01:26:39,671
l was wondering
if l could ask you a few questions.

995
01:26:39,839 --> 01:26:41,363
Well, that depends what they are.

996
01:26:41,541 --> 01:26:45,500
Oh, l see you're familiar
with our devious ways, aren't you?

997
01:26:46,246 --> 01:26:48,146
Okay, so l'll start
with something simple.

998
01:27:00,760 --> 01:27:03,422
And before that you were with
the South African Defense--?

999
01:27:03,596 --> 01:27:05,257
-Defense Force, correct.
-Of course.

1000
01:27:05,432 --> 01:27:08,868
And was that with Colonel Coetzee?
Were you in Angola?

1001
01:27:09,035 --> 01:27:10,559
Angola, yeah.

1002
01:27:12,172 --> 01:27:15,141
That is all l really need to know.
Thank you so much.

1003
01:27:15,341 --> 01:27:16,808
-Thank you.
-Okay.

1004
01:27:26,820 --> 01:27:28,219
Thank you, huh?

1005
01:27:28,388 --> 01:27:30,822
Just keeping my end of the deal.

1006
01:27:31,424 --> 01:27:32,721
Good luck to you, Solomon.

1007
01:27:33,026 --> 01:27:34,516
Okay.

1008
01:27:35,695 --> 01:27:39,529
-l hope you find what you're looking for.
-Thank you for all you have done.

1009
01:27:46,973 --> 01:27:49,567
-Listen, l--
-No, you listen.

1010
01:27:54,180 --> 01:27:56,080
ln another life maybe, all right?

1011
01:27:57,517 --> 01:27:59,348
Yeah. Sure.

1012
01:27:59,519 --> 01:28:00,884
Yeah.

1013
01:28:05,225 --> 01:28:07,352
You find yourself a good man,
all right, Maddy?

1014
01:28:13,299 --> 01:28:16,325
You know, l've got three sisters.

1015
01:28:16,503 --> 01:28:19,131
They're all married to good men.

1016
01:28:21,007 --> 01:28:22,065
l prefer my life.

1017
01:28:24,711 --> 01:28:29,171
Here is my office phone...

1018
01:28:29,349 --> 01:28:31,715
...home phone, cell phone.

1019
01:28:33,820 --> 01:28:36,983
l'm used to being pursued,
but what the heck.

1020
01:28:48,167 --> 01:28:50,294
You better get on that plane, huh?

1021
01:28:52,038 --> 01:28:53,938
You should get on that plane.

1022
01:29:02,115 --> 01:29:03,912
So should you.

1023
01:29:10,390 --> 01:29:11,516
You gonna call me?

1024
01:29:15,328 --> 01:29:16,818
Soon as l'm near a phone, yeah.

1025
01:29:17,764 --> 01:29:20,130
Yeah, right.

1026
01:29:41,955 --> 01:29:45,220
-Where is he?
-l don't know.

1027
01:29:49,796 --> 01:29:51,388
Oh, shit.

1028
01:29:51,664 --> 01:29:54,394
Nabil? Yeah, l'll call you
when we get closer, all right?

1029
01:29:54,567 --> 01:29:57,161
You keep me posted. Right.

1030
01:29:57,337 --> 01:30:01,137
All right. l set the pace, huh?
Two-hour marches, five-minute breaks.

1031
01:30:01,307 --> 01:30:05,141
lf l hold my hand up like this, you stop.
lf l point to the dirt, you lie flat.

1032
01:30:05,311 --> 01:30:08,872
lf l say go, you move like your life
depended on it. Understood?

1033
01:30:09,048 --> 01:30:11,710
-Yes, boss.
-Come on.

1034
01:30:21,995 --> 01:30:23,656
Tell me about the stone.

1035
01:30:23,830 --> 01:30:26,458
ls it clear or is it milky?

1036
01:30:26,633 --> 01:30:28,157
Clear.

1037
01:30:28,334 --> 01:30:30,734
And the color, is it strong?

1038
01:30:30,903 --> 01:30:32,131
Does it hold the light?

1039
01:30:32,305 --> 01:30:34,364
lt is as you say.

1040
01:30:34,807 --> 01:30:37,970
-About the size of a bird's egg?
-Yes.

1041
01:30:38,144 --> 01:30:42,308
One hundred carats.
Come on, let's pick up the pace.

1042
01:31:23,890 --> 01:31:25,255
Dia!

1043
01:31:27,160 --> 01:31:29,128
Stop the truck!

1044
01:31:29,896 --> 01:31:31,591
l thought it was Dia.

1045
01:32:25,518 --> 01:32:27,076
Wake up.

1046
01:32:28,921 --> 01:32:32,015
Don't worry, they're gone, huh?

1047
01:32:33,359 --> 01:32:36,487
You know, l once had this buddy...

1048
01:32:36,662 --> 01:32:38,527
...named Mabhoko.

1049
01:32:39,298 --> 01:32:42,529
We used to hunt bush meat
together as kids, huh?

1050
01:32:43,336 --> 01:32:44,701
Baboons.

1051
01:32:44,871 --> 01:32:47,738
Baboons, they were
the hardest to catch. They're....

1052
01:32:48,841 --> 01:32:50,172
They're cunning.

1053
01:32:50,343 --> 01:32:52,436
Cunning creatures.

1054
01:32:52,712 --> 01:32:55,340
Fast, strong.

1055
01:32:55,515 --> 01:32:57,745
Got good eyesight.

1056
01:32:58,251 --> 01:33:02,278
We would always find them
by the smell of their shit.

1057
01:33:02,455 --> 01:33:07,586
And that's how we learned to track
your black terrorists in Angola, huh?

1058
01:33:11,664 --> 01:33:13,097
By the smell of your shit.

1059
01:33:14,133 --> 01:33:15,600
lt's not....

1060
01:33:15,768 --> 01:33:18,498
lt's not the same as a baboon's.

1061
01:33:20,740 --> 01:33:24,301
But, you know, after you skin it...

1062
01:33:25,611 --> 01:33:27,841
...the flesh of a baboon...

1063
01:33:28,114 --> 01:33:30,514
...isn't that much different
than a man's, you know.

1064
01:33:33,920 --> 01:33:37,856
l'll tell you, l can track anything.

1065
01:33:50,102 --> 01:33:52,263
You risk my life like that again...

1066
01:33:57,643 --> 01:33:59,770
...and l'll peel your face
back off your head.

1067
01:34:02,281 --> 01:34:04,545
Do you understand?

1068
01:34:12,792 --> 01:34:14,851
Make us a fire.

1069
01:34:48,527 --> 01:34:51,985
Hello my brother. Are you lost?

1070
01:34:52,899 --> 01:34:54,730
We are headed for the mines in Kono.

1071
01:34:56,369 --> 01:35:00,430
You don't want to go that way. The
R.U.F. is in the next village.

1072
01:35:01,941 --> 01:35:03,408
Thank you, my brother.

1073
01:35:04,577 --> 01:35:07,341
And tell the poomui not to shoot me.

1074
01:35:09,615 --> 01:35:12,914
He is crazy for diamonds like everybody else.

1075
01:35:13,419 --> 01:35:15,284
Let's hope they don't discover oil here.

1076
01:35:17,623 --> 01:35:20,717
Then we'd have real problems.

1077
01:35:21,661 --> 01:35:22,685
Thank you, my brother.

1078
01:35:25,131 --> 01:35:26,723
What'd he say?

1079
01:35:26,899 --> 01:35:29,026
We are going the right way.

1080
01:35:36,175 --> 01:35:38,905
Hold up there, my man.
lt's this way, huh?

1081
01:35:40,379 --> 01:35:42,574
Where do you think you are going?

1082
01:35:44,250 --> 01:35:45,911
Stop!

1083
01:35:46,185 --> 01:35:47,880
l said, stop!

1084
01:35:48,321 --> 01:35:49,879
He is not down there, all right?

1085
01:35:51,924 --> 01:35:55,587
All right. You're gonna need
some of that old discipline, huh?

1086
01:35:55,761 --> 01:35:58,025
Now you listen here, my boy,
and you listen well.

1087
01:35:58,197 --> 01:36:00,165
You are not going down there.
Are we clear?

1088
01:36:00,333 --> 01:36:01,960
You are not the master.

1089
01:36:02,134 --> 01:36:05,763
Right now, that is exactly what l am,
and you'd better remember it, Kaffir!

1090
01:36:20,920 --> 01:36:22,251
Don't you fucking move, huh?

1091
01:36:22,421 --> 01:36:24,389
Don't you move. Don't you move, huh?

1092
01:36:24,557 --> 01:36:26,889
-My son is there!
-Your son is gone!

1093
01:36:27,059 --> 01:36:28,390
-He is alive!
-He's gone!

1094
01:36:28,561 --> 01:36:31,121
He's alive! He's there
with those crazy people!

1095
01:36:32,331 --> 01:36:35,767
l am his father! His father!
l should have protected him!

1096
01:36:36,235 --> 01:36:40,137
l must go find him.
l cannot live without knowing!

1097
01:36:40,306 --> 01:36:42,536
Shoot me if you want, but l'm going.

1098
01:36:44,643 --> 01:36:48,101
Why should it matter,
l'm dead already.

1099
01:36:55,955 --> 01:36:58,219
We wait until dark, huh?

1100
01:37:27,386 --> 01:37:28,785
Are you satisfied?

1101
01:37:31,757 --> 01:37:34,282
All right, come on.

1102
01:37:39,031 --> 01:37:41,226
--is fighting for Sierra Leone

1103
01:37:41,400 --> 01:37:44,460
RUF is fighting for Sierra Leone

1104
01:37:44,637 --> 01:37:47,572
Go tell my parents
They may see me no more

1105
01:37:47,740 --> 01:37:50,800
In the battlefield
We're fighting forever

1106
01:37:50,976 --> 01:37:53,877
Go tell my parents
They may see me no more

1107
01:37:54,046 --> 01:37:55,513
In the battlefield....

1108
01:37:58,084 --> 01:38:00,052
You are how old?

1109
01:38:00,219 --> 01:38:01,982
Me? l'm 31 .

1110
01:38:02,154 --> 01:38:04,315
And you have no wife?

1111
01:38:04,790 --> 01:38:07,657
-No.
-No children?

1112
01:38:08,828 --> 01:38:10,125
No.

1113
01:38:10,296 --> 01:38:11,923
And no home?

1114
01:38:12,098 --> 01:38:13,759
No.

1115
01:38:14,467 --> 01:38:16,867
But you have money, yes?

1116
01:38:17,036 --> 01:38:19,300
Yeah, some.

1117
01:38:19,472 --> 01:38:21,463
But not enough?

1118
01:38:23,976 --> 01:38:25,534
No.

1119
01:38:26,278 --> 01:38:30,772
lf you get this diamond,
you will have enough money, yes?

1120
01:38:32,918 --> 01:38:33,942
Yes.

1121
01:38:34,120 --> 01:38:36,918
Then you will get
a wife and children?

1122
01:38:37,089 --> 01:38:38,488
Probably not, no.

1123
01:38:40,559 --> 01:38:41,548
What?

1124
01:38:43,662 --> 01:38:45,186
What?

1125
01:38:45,598 --> 01:38:47,657
l am confused.

1126
01:38:48,734 --> 01:38:50,201
Yeah?

1127
01:38:50,369 --> 01:38:53,167
That makes two of us, my bru.

1128
01:38:55,674 --> 01:38:59,166
Oh, Christ.
l've gotta quit smoking, huh?

1129
01:38:59,778 --> 01:39:01,746
Why don't you?

1130
01:39:02,014 --> 01:39:04,414
l'll tell you what, Solomon.

1131
01:39:04,683 --> 01:39:09,211
You find me this diamond,
and l'll quit right then and there, huh?

1132
01:39:16,629 --> 01:39:19,621
-You were born in Zimbabwe?
-Oh, yeah.

1133
01:39:19,798 --> 01:39:22,961
-ls it beautiful there?
-Sure you're not a reporter?

1134
01:39:23,369 --> 01:39:26,827
Because you ask a hell of a lot
of questions, my man.

1135
01:39:34,480 --> 01:39:38,177
My grandfather told
many stories of war.

1136
01:39:38,417 --> 01:39:41,250
How the Mende fought the Temne.

1137
01:39:41,420 --> 01:39:45,151
Or how two tribes would fight
when somebody had stolen a woman.

1138
01:39:55,234 --> 01:39:58,601
l understand white people
want our diamonds, yes?

1139
01:40:01,640 --> 01:40:05,371
But how can my own people
do this to each other?

1140
01:40:13,652 --> 01:40:15,711
l know good people...

1141
01:40:15,888 --> 01:40:18,755
...who say there is something
wrong with us...

1142
01:40:19,124 --> 01:40:20,284
...inside our black skin.

1143
01:40:20,459 --> 01:40:23,792
That we were better off
when the white man ruled.

1144
01:40:25,698 --> 01:40:28,496
But my son is good.

1145
01:40:30,069 --> 01:40:32,264
And when he grows up...

1146
01:40:32,438 --> 01:40:33,666
...and peace comes...

1147
01:40:37,676 --> 01:40:40,338
...this place will be a paradise.

1148
01:40:48,220 --> 01:40:50,688
We'll get your son back, huh?

1149
01:41:32,398 --> 01:41:34,730
Where is it exactly?

1150
01:41:36,268 --> 01:41:39,169
Through the camp, by the river.

1151
01:41:43,776 --> 01:41:45,471
Christ.

1152
01:41:45,944 --> 01:41:47,571
Okay.

1153
01:41:48,213 --> 01:41:50,078
l'm gonna make contact
with the colonel.

1154
01:41:50,249 --> 01:41:51,773
He'll send in an air strike.

1155
01:41:52,217 --> 01:41:55,186
-What is that?
-A chopper, huh? An attack helicopter.

1156
01:41:55,354 --> 01:41:57,879
-We use it as a diversion.
-What if my son is there?

1157
01:41:58,057 --> 01:41:59,354
-He isn't.
-How do you know?

1158
01:41:59,525 --> 01:42:03,120
l said we do it my way now, all right?
Don't fuck with me.

1159
01:42:13,038 --> 01:42:15,438
Cordell, it's Danny.

1160
01:42:15,607 --> 01:42:17,939
Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Shut up and listen, all right?

1161
01:42:18,110 --> 01:42:20,977
You tell the colonel l've found the stone.

1162
01:42:21,146 --> 01:42:24,115
No, l haven't got it in my hands,
but l'm OP-ing its location.

1163
01:42:24,283 --> 01:42:25,875
lt's a major rebel camp, my man.

1164
01:42:26,051 --> 01:42:28,417
You tell him to send in the dakadak.

1165
01:42:28,987 --> 01:42:31,854
Because l stole a GPS, that's how.

1166
01:42:32,024 --> 01:42:34,584
lf you shut up and listen,
l could give the coordinates.

1167
01:42:35,027 --> 01:42:38,053
Zero-nine-zero-five-four-two-four, north.

1168
01:42:38,230 --> 01:42:42,792
Three-two-seven-two-nine
three-zero-five-zero, east.

1169
01:42:42,968 --> 01:42:45,232
l'll call back at midnight to confirm.

1170
01:42:48,006 --> 01:42:50,941
You can look all night,
my friend, right?

1171
01:42:51,110 --> 01:42:53,772
l promise you he is not there.

1172
01:42:59,017 --> 01:43:01,212
They're coming in the morning, all right?

1173
01:43:01,387 --> 01:43:03,821
No movement, my friend. You stay still.

1174
01:43:05,758 --> 01:43:08,192
When it gets dark,
then we move in closer.

1175
01:43:30,349 --> 01:43:33,341
Solomon. Shit.

1176
01:43:44,129 --> 01:43:45,528
l can do it.

1177
01:43:45,697 --> 01:43:46,789
-Help me.
-Help him.

1178
01:43:46,965 --> 01:43:49,024
Thank you, Papa.

1179
01:44:30,976 --> 01:44:33,206
Hey, you smell.

1180
01:44:34,413 --> 01:44:35,880
That's fine.

1181
01:44:48,193 --> 01:44:50,161
-Ready? l'm winning.
-Okay, let's go.

1182
01:44:50,329 --> 01:44:51,990
Play, man.

1183
01:44:53,565 --> 01:44:56,466
-Play. Play the card.
-Play.

1184
01:45:23,262 --> 01:45:24,388
Dia.

1185
01:45:27,432 --> 01:45:29,127
Leave me alone.

1186
01:45:30,168 --> 01:45:33,399
-Dia. l'm your papa. Come with me.
-Hey.

1187
01:45:33,572 --> 01:45:35,301
-Dia.
-Get away from me.

1188
01:45:35,474 --> 01:45:37,271
-Dia. Dia!
-l do not know you. Traitor!

1189
01:45:37,643 --> 01:45:40,134
-Enemy! Enemy!
-What the hell are you doing?

1190
01:45:40,312 --> 01:45:41,540
-What are you doing?
-l don't know you!

1191
01:45:41,713 --> 01:45:43,010
-What's wrong?
-l hate you!

1192
01:45:43,181 --> 01:45:44,910
-Dia, come with me!
-l hate you!

1193
01:45:45,083 --> 01:45:46,607
Get away from me!

1194
01:45:49,087 --> 01:45:50,952
-Get him!
-Don't shoot!

1195
01:45:51,456 --> 01:45:53,686
-Don't shoot! Don't--! Don't shoot!
-l hate you!

1196
01:45:53,859 --> 01:45:55,759
-Fisherman! Traitor!
-Don't shoot!

1197
01:45:55,928 --> 01:45:58,158
Get away from me!

1198
01:46:05,270 --> 01:46:07,431
l knew you would come back.

1199
01:46:07,906 --> 01:46:11,398
l have dug and dug and dug,
but l've found nothing.

1200
01:46:11,577 --> 01:46:13,477
Nothing.

1201
01:46:13,745 --> 01:46:15,235
Dig, dig, dig!

1202
01:46:15,414 --> 01:46:17,712
You will find it for me.

1203
01:46:18,684 --> 01:46:20,982
You will dig up
what you have come back for.

1204
01:46:21,153 --> 01:46:22,177
No.

1205
01:46:22,354 --> 01:46:24,788
Why should the diamond
go to the foreign devils?

1206
01:46:25,524 --> 01:46:28,789
We will use it
to make the country strong.

1207
01:46:29,261 --> 01:46:31,855
RUF is fighting for the people!

1208
01:46:34,199 --> 01:46:37,293
RUF is fighting for Sierra Leone!

1209
01:46:40,138 --> 01:46:41,867
Pick it up.

1210
01:46:43,075 --> 01:46:46,044
Why? You are going to kill me anyway.

1211
01:46:46,211 --> 01:46:49,305
l do not need to kill you,
Solomon Vandy.

1212
01:46:52,150 --> 01:46:54,345
lf you do not bring me the diamond...

1213
01:46:54,519 --> 01:46:56,749
...l will find the rest of your family.

1214
01:46:56,922 --> 01:46:59,356
